1. Install ufw(if it is not already installed)

sudo apt update
sudo apt install ufw

2. Set up the firewall rules to allow incoming traffic on ports 22 (SSH), 443 (HTTPS), and 80 (HTTP), while blocking all other incoming traffic:

sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw allow 22/tcp
sudo ufw allow 443/tcp
sudo ufw allow 80/tcp

3. Enable the firewall to apply the rules:

sudo ufw enable

4. Verify the status of ufw to ensure the rules are in place:

sudo ufw status
